Hochtief’s Noe Quit After ACS Nominated Board Members, FTD Says

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-03-14T07:24:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/hochtief-s-noe-quit-after-acs-nominated-board-members-ftd-says.html
  Hochtief AG (HOT) ’s concessions chief,
Peter Noe, quit after Actividades de Construccion & Servicios
SA, which is buying the builder, presented a list of candidates
for the supervisory board,  Financial Times Deutschland said ,
citing an unidentified person familiar with the situation.  The list left no room for doubt about ACS’s resolve to take
power at Essen, Germany-based Hochtief, the newspaper said. Noe,
who is leaving on Sept. 10, is making use of a change-of-control
clause which allows executives to receive a severance package of
2 1/2 years of salary, FTD said.  Noe’s departure is not a sign that Chief Executive Officer
Herbert Luetkestratkoetter will leave, an unidentified company
spokeswoman said, according to the German newspaper.  Christian Gerhardus, a Hochtief spokesman, declined to
comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
